From the relationships, we can deduce the following chain:

• Lisa is Martha’s ancestor (given) and Martha is an ancestor of Timothy (given).
• Timothy is an ancestor of Dennis (given) and Dennis is an ancestor of Elizabeth (given). This forms the chain: Lisa → Martha → Timothy → Dennis → Elizabeth.
• Randy is Lisa’s ancestor (given), so Randy is above Lisa.
• Randy is a descendant of Sarah (given), which means Sarah is an ancestor of Randy.
• Barbara is an ancestor of Sarah (given).

Putting it all together, we get the full chain:
  Barbara → Sarah → Randy → Lisa → Martha → Timothy → Dennis → Elizabeth

Thus, Elizabeth is a descendant of Barbara.
